# Docker local verification

After finishing a task, verify it by running the local Docker stack unless the user explicitly says not to.

1. Run `docker compose up --build -d` from the repo root.
2. Smoke-test the changed behavior (API calls, page loads, or relevant endpoints).
3. Report build/startup failures and fix them before considering the task done.
4. Skip Docker verification only when the user asks not to run it.
